text: Lincoln is a city in Placer County, California, United States. It grew 282.1 percent between 2000 and 2010, making it the fastest growing city over 10,000 people in the United States. The population was 49,757 at the 2020 census. == References == Category:1850s establishments in California Category:1890 establishments in California Category:1859 establishments in the United States Category:Cities in California Category:Settlements in Placer County, California
